President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Earl W. Gast is nominated for Assistant Administrator for Africa at the United States Agency for International Development (USAID). Roberta S. Jacobson is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Western Hemisphere Affairs at the Department of State. Michael T. Scuse is nominated for Under Secretary for Farm and Foreign Agricultural Services at the Department of Agriculture. Additionally, Glen F. Post III is appointed as a member of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. President Obama expressed confidence in the capabilities of these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future.